  "description": {
    "lang": "eng",
    "value": "Code Injection in GitHub repository pytorchlightning/pytorch-lightning prior to 1.6.0.\n\nReason for inclusion in AVID: CVE-2022-0845 describes a code injection vulnerability in the PyTorch Lightning library (pytorch-lightning) prior to version 1.6.0. PyTorch Lightning is a widely-used framework in AI model development and training, making this a software supply-chain issue for general-purpose AI systems. The vulnerability is clearly a security vulnerability (code execution risk) with CVSS metrics provided, and the report includes references and a patch commit, indicating sufficient evidence for curation."
  },
